nit: better name might be to call this is a SkipList, and to make it generic across bindings. Also, instead of passing these as two uint8_t parameters, please pass these as an array of bytes. They can be interpreted as per the binding's wish.
Done
Default should be a failure..
unwanted line?

We don't have to be explicitly state this.

You can state the reason as - for few of the validation test cases, it is advantageous to stop MCTP communications to a specific PCIe slot. Thus, this patch adds an OEM IPMI command to enable/disable MCTP communication to specific PCIe slot (under manufacturing mode).
May be use a local variable to store this long repetitive string.
shouldn't this be return muxSlotDisable(ctx, mctpHsbpService, "HSBP_Mux", enable, slotNum); ?
Minor bug, Other code ltgm.
Invalid argument might be a better option. The user provided information that does not match what was expected.
Again, invalid argument might be better here. The response from getBusNumFromPath depends wholly upon the difference between the user input and the paths existing on the BMC.
res is unused and ec is unchecked.
